value.value: アブミ骨閉鎖孔の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the central foramen (hole) located between the crura and the footplate of the stapes through which the stapedial artery passes
アブミ骨閉鎖孔の矮小化
reduced size of the central foramen (hole) located between the crura and the footplate of the stapes through which the stapedial artery passes
アブミ骨閉鎖孔の欠如
missing the central foramen (hole) located between the crura and the footplate of the stapes through which the stapedial artery passes
アブミ骨前後脚の形態異常

any structural anomaly of either of the two (anterior and posterior) limbs of the stapes that pass from the head to the base or footplate; in mice, the anterior crus is curved and the posterior crus is more straight whereas in humans, the anterior crus is more straight than the posterior crus
アブミ骨後脚の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the generally longer arching stem of the stapes that projects medially from the neck, forming the posterior border of the bone, and joins the flat, disc-like base
アブミ骨前脚の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the generally shorter stem of the stapes that projects medially from the neck, forming the anterior border of the bone, and joins the flat, disc-like base
滲出性中耳炎
fluid accumulation in the middle ear cavity due to dysfunction of the Eustachian tube

fluid may be serous, mucoid, bloody, purulent or any combination thereof; the term does not distinguish between effusions due to acute otitis media (AOM) and effusions due to otitis media with effusion (OME)
正円窓（蝸牛窓）の矮小化

less than average size of the opening on the medial wall of the middle ear leading into the cochlea, closed in life by the secondary tympanic membrane; it serves to regulate fluid pressure in the inner ear
正円窓（蝸牛窓）の欠如
absence of the opening on the medial wall of the middle ear leading into the cochlea, closed in life by the secondary tympanic membrane; it serves to regulate fluid pressure in the inner ear
鼓膜の退縮

a condition in which a segment of the tympanic membrane (eardrum) collapses inwards towards the middle ear space and lies more medially (deeper) than its normal position; the retracted segment is often known as a retraction pocket
鼓膜の穿孔
presence of a hole or tear in the tympanic membrane (eardrum)
上顎間縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the anterior median suture between the two maxillae of the upper jawbone, located between the inferior border of the nasal aperture and the central incisor teeth
側頭骨の頬骨突起の欠如
missing the long, arched process that projects from the lower region of the squamous part of the temporal bone and articulates with the zygomatic bone
頭蓋顔面骨の過形成
excessive growth of the craniofacial bones
顔面骨の過形成
excessive growth of the facial bones
耳垢過多
excess buildup of cerumen, a yellowish waxy substance (earwax), in the external auditory canal
頭蓋底の短縮
decreased length of the anterior and/or posterior portions of the skull base
舌筋の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the tongue muscle, typically resulting in decreased size
外耳の軟骨組織の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the elastic cartilage components of the auricles and/or external acoustic meatus
耳介軟骨の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the elastic cartilage component of the auricles
口蓋上顎縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the transverse suture across the back of the hard palate that separates the maxillary shelf of the palate from the horizontal plates of the palatine bones
上顎間縫合の拡大
an abnormally increased width of the anterior median suture between the two maxillae of the upper jawbone for age-related norms
顔面筋形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the facial muscle, typically resulting in decreased size
頚筋の形態異常
any structural anomaly of any skeletal muscle that is part of the cervical (neck) region
斜角筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of any of the three pairs of muscles in the lateral neck, namely the scalenus anterior, scalenus medius, and scalenus posterior; the scalenes are innervated by the cervical spinal nerves C4-C8, act as accessory muscles of respiration, and perform flexion at the neck
上唇挙筋の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the flat, thin muscle lying beneath the skin on the lateral surface of the maxillary bone; it arises from the maxillary bone, over the dorsum of the nose, and runs cranioventrally to insert partly on the wing of the nostril and partly into the lateral part of the upper lip; it acts to dilate the nostrils and elevate and retract the upper lip
上唇挙筋の欠如

missing the flat, thin muscle that lies beneath the skin on the lateral surface of the maxillary bone; it arises from the maxillary bone, over the dorsum of the nose, and runs cranioventrally to insert partly on the wing of the nostril and partly into the lateral part of the upper lip; it acts to dilate the nostrils and elevate and retract the upper lip
前頭縫合の拡大
an abnormally increased width of the metopic suture for age-related norms
頭蓋骨の卵円孔の拡大
increased size of the oval-shaped opening in the middle cranial fossa located at the posterior base of the greater wing of the sphenoid bone, lateral to the lingula of the mandible
正円孔の拡大
increased size of the circular hole (foramen) in the sphenoid bone that connects the middle cranial fossa and the pterygopalatine fossa
切歯縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the maxillary-premaxillary suture, the line of union of the two portions of the maxilla (pre- and postmaxilla)
頭蓋顔面縫合の早期癒合
early closure of any joint (suture) between cranial and/or facial bones
前頭鼻骨縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the joint (suture) between the frontal bone and the two nasal bones
骨芽細胞の増殖異常

anomaly in the ability of osteoblasts to undergo expansion by cell division; osteoblasts are skeletogenic cells that secrete osteoid, are capable of producing mineralized (hydroxyapatite) matrix, are located adjacent to or within osteoid tissue, and arise from the transformation of a preosteoblast cell
骨芽細胞の増殖増加

increase in the expansion rate of osteoblasts by cell division; osteoblasts are skeletogenic cells that secrete osteoid, are capable of producing mineralized (hydroxyapatite) matrix, are located adjacent to or within osteoid tissue, and arise from the transformation of a preosteoblast cell
骨芽細胞の増殖減少

reduction in the expansion rate of osteoblasts by cell division; osteoblasts are skeletogenic cells that secrete osteoid, are capable of producing mineralized (hydroxyapatite) matrix, are located adjacent to or within osteoid tissue, and arise from the transformation of a preosteoblast cell
骨芽細胞のアポトーシス異常

change in the timing or the number of osteoblasts undergoing programmed cell death; osteoblasts are skeletogenic cells that secrete osteoid, are capable of producing mineralized (hydroxyapatite) matrix, are located adjacent to or within osteoid tissue, and arise from the transformation of a preosteoblast cell
骨芽細胞のアポトーシス増加
increase in the number of osteoblasts undergoing programmed cell death
骨芽細胞のアポトーシス減少
reduction in the number of osteoblasts undergoing programmed cell death
頭蓋の軟骨結合の異常

any anomaly in the development of cartilaginous joints or growth centers between bones of the skull base by the formation of hyaline cartilage which is abundant during the growth phase and ultimately ossifies during skeletal maturation; synchondroses are composed of mirror-image growth plates with a central resting zone, proliferative zones, and hypertrophic zones on both sides; in mouse, there are two synchondroses in the midline cranial base, the sphenooccipital and presphenoidal synchondroses
頭蓋の軟骨結合の早期癒合

early fusion or ossification of one or more cranial base synchondroses relative to age- and gender-matched controls; can lead to midface hypoplasia, as seen in patients with specific forms of syndromic craniosynostosis
蝶後頭軟骨結合の異常

any anomaly in the development of the cartilaginous joint (growth center) between the basioccipital and basisphenoid bones that is an important driver of facial and cranial base growth; sphenooccipital synchondroses are among the last to fuse and may remain patent until early adulthood
蝶後頭軟骨結合の早期癒合

early closure or ossification of the sphenooccipital synchondrosis relative to age- and gender-matched controls; premature fusion has been associated with midface hypoplasia in animal models and patients with specific forms of syndromic craniosynostosis
前蝶形骨の軟骨結合異常
any anomaly in the development of the cartilaginous joint (growth center) between the presphenoid and basisphenoid bones of the skull base
前蝶形骨の軟骨結合早期癒合
early closure or ossification of the presphenoid synchondrosis relative to age- and gender-matched controls
歯強直
solid fixation of a tooth resulting from fusion of the dental cementum and alveolar bone, with obliteration of the periodontal ligament
エナメルの石灰化異常
anomaly in the process by which calcium salts, mainly carbonated hydroxyapatite, are deposited into the dental enamel
象牙質の石灰化異常
anomaly in the process by which calcium salts are deposited into dentin
セメント質の石灰化異常
anomaly in the process by which calcium salts, mainly carbonated hydroxyapatite, are deposited into the initial acellular cementum
象牙芽細胞の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the skeletogenic cell on the outer surface of the dental pulp that secretes dentin matrix, is derived from the odontogenic papilla, and develops from a preodontoblast cell
